prompt.core_definition:
A course is PIT_RELATED when its central purpose, major themes, assignments, applications, or learning outcomes combine BOTH:

1. A meaningful technology component:
   computing, AI, data science, digital systems, software, cybersecurity, information systems, human-centered technical design, platforms, digital media systems, computational social science, technology policy, technology governance, engineering systems, scientific technologies, health technologies, energy technologies, assistive technologies, or other applied technical systems.

2. A central public-interest component:
   public benefit, public problems, government, civic life, democracy, elections, public-sector technology, nonprofit/community partner work, accessibility, inclusion, civil rights, racial justice, social justice, public health, education access, environmental sustainability or justice, information integrity, privacy/civil liberties, legal access, housing, food security, safety from online harms, accountable technology, responsible deployment, or equitable technology governance.

A course is NOT_PIT_RELATED if it has:
- technology without a central public-interest purpose;
- public/social/legal/ethical discussion without a meaningful technology component;
- a broad overview of a technology and its social impacts;
- a law/business/IP course about a technology sector;
- generic technical, design, product, or professional training;
- only hypothetical, incidental, or example public-interest applications.
